From 183d8186d5452142e92ffee053bc313884d00c36 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Stoyan Kushlev <skushlev@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 17:42:08 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] Fix camera metadata headers for linux embedded
 compilation

In linux embedded ANDROID_API is not defined and cutils/compiler.h
and <log/log.h> are not defined, those are specific android headers
and defines, needed only for android compilation.

Remove ANDROID_API, cutils/compiler.h and <log/log.h> from
camera_metadata.h, camera_metadata.c and camera_metadata_hidden.h
to build the libcamera_metadata.so

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Yocto specific change]

Signed-off-by: Stoyan Kushlev <skushlev@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 camera/include/system/camera_metadata.h       | 42 -------------------
 camera/src/camera_metadata.c                  |  4 +-
 .../camera/include/camera_metadata_hidden.h   |  9 ----
 3 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 52 deletions(-)

